title: 26-4: Station "Motor-Boating" CATER 155344
text: ACR called about station "motor-boating". At first tried ranging the thyratron, seemed to make the PFN jitter worse. DQ'ging current was unstable, so HV regulator was swapped as it seemed the adjustment pot was flaky. Not so. Decided to open station up for inspection and viola! Saw that all 6 carborundum resistors were gone, with 2 of them totally destroyed. Upper clips on thyrite assembly showed signs of overheating. Found that the screws were basically only hand tight. PFN caps were also checked for any signs of leaking or swelling - NTF. Replaced all 6 upper clips and resistors, buttoned up station, and turned it back on. At 18kV, got high limit on thyratron at 4.5V (adjusted remotely but not documented), so I lowered Vres to 4.3V. High limit gone, jitter almost nothing. Slowly raised HV to BV's back to 350kV (was 340kV). Re-saturated klystron, station looks good. Note: Original problem (besides resistors) was the thyratron Vres was too high, causing the PFN to become unstable. ct/rm
